stmodern fiction from both thematic and formal perspectives, giving in-depth coverage to key features and issues such as metafiction, the relation to modernism, history, and politicsFeatures work by some of the most important theorists and critics of the last few decades, such as Ihab Hassan, Jean Baudrillard, Linda Hutcheon, and Brian McHaleProvides a sense of historical, social and cultural context to the debate about postmodernism in fictionGives ample coverage to some of the most compelling issues raised in relation to postmodern fiction in recent years, such as science and new technologies, the cyborg, 'race' and gender  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPostmodernism (Literature). 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAppiah, Kwame Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBakhtin, Mikhail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarth, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarthes, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaudrillard, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDocherty, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEco, Umberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFiedler, Leslie A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraff, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaraway, Donna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarvey, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHassan, lhab, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHollinger, Veronica, 